Himmelhoch-A.

The effects of chronic illness on children of 0-3 years and their
families.

ADAPTATION-PSYCHOLOGICAL.  CHRONIC-DISEASE.
PARENT-CHILD-RELATIONS.

AFFECTIVE-SYMPTOMS.  CHILD-PRESCHOOL.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS.  HUMAN.
INFANT.  INFANT-NEWBORN.  MENTAL-RETARDATION.  NEOPLASMS.

I have taken as examples of chronic illness in infancy four
different types of disability: emotional deprivation, infants with
sub-normal development, children suffering from mucodiscoidosis, and
children who have neoplastic disease.

